=== More Technical Information ===

The technical pipeline, architecture, debate-flow, and data-model are in the technical appendix at the end of this document.

----

== Where We Stand ==

**Working in Alpha:** Full 5-stage pipeline operational end-to-end — multi-provider debate, quality gates, UCM configuration, 7 search providers, multilingual analysis (DE/EN/FR/PT), input neutrality (±4%), and structured HTML reports.

**Main gaps:** Performance (~15 min, target < 5 min), report stability (LLM stochasticity + live evidence), user authentication, horizontal scaling, and cost reduction ($0.15-0.25 per analysis, target < $0.05).

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Research opportunity:** Report stability is a measurable problem — formal stability metrics, tolerance bands, and reproducibility protocols for LLM-based fact-checking.
)))

=== Key Facts ===

|=Metric|=Value
|Pipeline stages|5 + optional Stage 4.5 (SR Calibration), with 2 mandatory quality gates
|Debate steps per claim|5 (adversarial, multi-provider)
|LLM providers|4 integrated (Anthropic Sonnet 4.5 + OpenAI GPT-4.1 active in debate; Google Gemini + Mistral available)
|Search providers|7 (Google CSE, Serper, SerpAPI, Brave, Wikipedia, Semantic Scholar, Google Fact Check)
|Verdict scale|7-point (TRUE to FALSE) with 4 confidence tiers
|LLM calls per analysis|~40-50
|Languages|Multi-language input and evidence (EN, DE, FR, PT, ...)
|License / posture|Open-source, public-interest oriented, fully transparent

