== Cooperation Opportunities ==

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Best collaboration starting points:**

* **Small models for high-volume subtasks** — strongest lever for latency and cost
* **Low-latency retrieval / RAG** — strongest lever for interactive-speed evidence acquisition
* **Evaluation and reproducibility** — establish FactHarbor as a benchmarked, publishable research platform; co-develop evaluation sets and ground-truth annotations
* **Prototype-and-measure** — test high-leverage improvements directly in FactHarbor with fast feedback loops
* **Student theses and publications** — focused subprojects and shared-task submissions as low-risk starting points
)))

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Medium- and longer-term directions**:

* **Reproducible fact-checking testbed** — per-job config snapshots and configurable stages enable publishable baseline-vs-variant studies
* **Real-Time Fact Checking** — later-stage goal: live verification of audio, video, and mixed media
* **Federated fact-checking** — reconcile conflicting verdicts across independent instances in a decentralized network
* **Community and collaboration** — expert input, joint annotation, comparative views, team workflows
)))

