== Why Collaborate: Mutual Benefits ==

Collaboration is not one-directional — both sides bring what the other needs.

=== What the Research Partner Gains ===

|=Benefit|=Why It Matters
|**Working alpha testbed**|End-to-end on real claims with inspectable artifacts — honest about Alpha-stage limitations
|**Modular research platform**|Each pipeline stage produces intermediate artifacts; all parameters configurable via UCM with per-job config snapshots
|**Domain-agnostic scope**|Unlike Climinator (climate-only), HAMiSoN (social media), or CheckThat! (shared-task benchmark), FactHarbor is **general-domain and topic-agnostic**
|**Publishable open problems**|Pipeline distillation, multilingual verdict stability, evidence sufficiency, report stability, cross-provider debate dynamics
|**Applied implementation partner**|Concrete implementation partner and real-world validation environment for collaborative projects
|**Open-source visibility**|Visible, citable, reusable — not locked behind a corporate NDA

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Summary:** Research partners mainly gain a modular, topic-agnostic Alpha-stage research testbed with real artifacts, concrete open problems, and a plausible applied implementation partner.
)))

=== What FactHarbor Gains ===

|=Benefit|=Why It Matters
|**Rigorous evaluation**|Formal benchmarks (ViClaim, CheckThat!, DIRAS, ACL 2024)
|**Research framing**|Turn internal quality work into publishable evaluation questions, framed as "resource-efficient fact verification"
|**Research infrastructure**|University compute, multilingual NLP datasets, academic networks
|**Grant vehicle**|Innosuisse, SNSF, Hasler, BRIDGE, Horizon Europe — depending on partner and scope
|**Publication pipeline**|Joint papers at ACL, EMNLP, CLEF CheckThat! — ViClaim (EMNLP 2025 main) shows this works
|**Student contributors**|Bachelor/Master theses on specific pipeline components — low-risk exploration

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Summary:** FactHarbor mainly gains formal evaluation methods, research framing, infrastructure access, and credible paths to funding and publications.
)))

