== FactHarbor Roadmap ==

FactHarbor is currently in **Alpha**.

|=Phase|=Status|=Milestones
|**POC**|Completed|Single host, full pipeline operational
|**Alpha**|Current|Invite-code access, rate limiting, pre-release hardening
|**Beta**|Planned|User authentication, horizontal scaling, monitoring
|**V1.0**|Planned|Public REST API, observability, disaster recovery
|**V2.0+**|Vision|Federation, semantic search, distributed consensus

=== V1.0 Engineering Goals ===

|=Goal|=Current|=Target
|**Performance**|~5 min per analysis|< 90 seconds via caching and parallel execution
|**Cost**|~$0.15-0.25 per analysis|< $0.05 via caching, smaller models, evidence reuse
|**Scalability**|Single host, 3 concurrent jobs|Horizontal scaling, queue-based dispatch
|**Repeatability**|Verdicts vary across runs|Tolerance bands, evidence caching
|**Stability**|Manual recovery|Auto-recovery, health monitoring

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Research angle:** These goals create measurable constraints for "resource-efficient fact verification" — speed/cost motivate small-model substitution, repeatability motivates reproducibility work.
)))

=== Beyond V1.0 ===

|=Direction|=Key capabilities|=Target
|**Platform integrations**|REST API, browser extensions, widgets, ClaimReview, mobile|V1.0 – V1.5+
|**Advanced analysis**|Image/video verification, semantic search, evidence reuse|V1.1+ – V2.0+
|**Community**|Expert review, collaborative annotation, team workspaces|V1.5+ – V2.0+
|**Federation**|Claim sync, distributed verdict consensus, contradiction detection|V2.0+
|**SR as a service**|Standalone Source Reliability API for external consumers|V1.5+

