== Appendix: Target User Groups ==

|=User Group|=How They Use FactHarbor|=Key Need
|**General Public**|Browse published analyses, explore the evidence landscape — no registration required|Transparent, accessible verdicts they can verify themselves
|**Journalists & Content Creators**|Fact-check claims before publishing; cite FactHarbor verdicts with full provenance|API access, speed, credibility — evidence chains they can reference in their work
|**Researchers & Academics**|Filter by verification status, confidence levels, source quality; export data for studies|Audit trails, reproducible results, exportable structured data
|**Social Media Users**|Quick-check claims before sharing to avoid spreading misinformation|Fast turnaround, clear verdicts, easy to understand
|**Educators**|Use real-world claim analyses as teaching material for critical thinking and media literacy|Multi-perspective evidence landscapes, not just binary verdicts

(% class="box infomessage" %)
(((
**Design principle:** Anyone can browse without registration. Submission requires only a free account. Every verdict is fully transparent.
)))

== Appendix: Current Status Detail ==

=== What Works ===

|=Area|=Status|=Details
|**CB Pipeline (all 5 stages)**|Working in Alpha|Extract Claims, Research, Cluster Boundaries, Verdict, Aggregate — operational end-to-end
|**Multi-Provider LLM Debate**|Working|Anthropic advocate + OpenAI challenger, self-consistency, reconciler, validator
|**Quality Gates (Gate 1 + Gate 4)**|Working|Claim validation and confidence tiering with UI panel
|**UCM Configuration**|Working|All analysis parameters tunable at runtime, hot-reloadable, per-job config snapshots
|**Source Reliability v2**|Working|LLM-powered assessment and cache isolation active; SR weighting and Stage 4.5 disabled pending validation
|**Multi-Provider Search**|Working|7 providers (web, Wikipedia, Semantic Scholar, Google Fact Check); automatic fallback
|**LLM Model Tiering**|Working|Budget models for extraction, standard for verdicts, cross-provider challenger
|**Multilingual Analysis**|Working|DE, EN, FR, PT tested; no English-only logic
|**Input Neutrality**|Working|"Was X fair?" vs "X was fair" within ±4%
|**HTML Report Generation**|Working|Structured reports with evidence citations, per-boundary findings

=== What's Open ===

|=Area|=Status|=What's Needed
|**User Authentication**|Not started|Invite-code only; needs user accounts, OAuth, RBAC
|**Performance**|Needs improvement|~5 min per claim; target < 90s via caching and parallelism
|**Repeatability**|Partial|Self-consistency gating done; evidence caching and tolerance bands needed
|**Observability**|Partial|Metrics working; dashboards and alerting not yet set up
|**Horizontal Scaling**|Not started|Single-host only; needs queue-based dispatch
|**Claim Caching**|Partial|Search caching working; full evidence reuse planned (30-50% savings)

=== Known Problems ===

|=Factor|=Cause|=Mitigation Status
|**LLM Stochasticity**|Temperature 0 outputs not fully deterministic|Self-consistency check measures stability; high spread reduces confidence
|**Live Web Evidence**|Sources change daily|Evidence caching planned but not built
|**Claim Decomposition Variance**|Same input → different AtomicClaims|Two-pass extraction reduces but doesn't eliminate variance

|=Problem|=Details
|**Over-decomposition**|Rhetorical claims sometimes decomposed too aggressively
|**SR evaluation quality**|Not yet benchmarked against human expert assessments
|**Cost per analysis**|$0.15-0.25 — acceptable for Alpha, too high for public scale

