{{/mermaid}}

=== Pipeline Stages and Model Tiering ===

|=Stage|=Name|=What Happens|=Model Tier
|1|**Extract Claims**|Pass 1 scan, preliminary web grounding, Pass 2 grounded extraction, centrality filter, Gate 1 validation|Budget + Web Search
|2|**Research**|Iterative query generation, web search, relevance screening, source fetch, evidence extraction, and evidence filtering|Budget + Web Search
|3|**Cluster Boundaries**|Collect scopes, optionally normalize equivalent scopes, then cluster into ClaimAssessmentBoundaries|Budget + Standard
|4|**Verdict**|5-step adversarial LLM debate per claim (see below)|Sonnet (standard)
|4.5|//**SR Calibration**// (optional)|An optional calibration path exists for LLM-backed source portfolio adjustment, but it remains disabled by default pending validation.|Budget
|5|**Aggregate**|Weighted aggregation with triangulation, narrative generation|Sonnet (standard)

=== LLM Call Topology ===

|=Pipeline Part|=Typical Call Pattern
|**Stage 1: Claim extraction**|Pass 1 scan + Pass 2 evidence-grounded extraction + Gate 1 validation (batched budget-tier calls)
|**Stage 2: Research**|Repeated budget-tier calls for query generation, relevance classification, and evidence extraction across search rounds
|**Stage 3: Boundary clustering**|Scope normalization plus clustering calls to form ClaimAssessmentBoundaries
|**Stage 4: Verdict debate**|1 advocate + 2 self-consistency re-runs + 1 challenger + 1 reconciler + 2 lightweight validator checks
|**Stage 5: Final report**|Aggregation / narrative generation call for the published result

=== Loop and Retry Topology ===

The production pipeline contains multiple control-flow loops and retries beyond the simplified sufficiency-check arrow shown above.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TB
    subgraph S1["Stage 1: Claim Extraction Loops"]
        direction LR
        P1["Pass 1 scan"]:::llmCall
        PRE["Preliminary web grounding"]:::searchCall
        P2["Pass 2 grounded extraction"]:::llmCall
        P2R["Pass 2 retry / fallback\n(hardcoded retry limit)"]:::llmCall
        G1["Gate 1 validation"]:::llmCall
        ENOUGH{"Enough claims\npost-Gate 1?"}:::decision
        REP["Reprompt Pass 2 + Gate 1\n(UCM-configured attempts)"]:::llmCall

        P1 -->|"rough claims"| PRE -->|"preliminary evidence"| P2 -->|"candidate claims"| G1 -->|"validated claims"| ENOUGH
        P2 -.->|"soft refusal / schema issue"| P2R -->|"retry context"| P2
        ENOUGH -->|"No"| REP -->|"guidance + input"| P2
    end

    subgraph S2["Stage 2: Research Iteration Loops"]
        direction TB
        MAIN{"Continue main loop?\n(sufficiency, time,\nbudget, zero-yield)"}:::decision
        PICK["Pick least-researched claim"]:::neutral

        subgraph ITER["Per-iteration research"]
            direction LR
            QGEN["Generate queries"]:::llmCall
            SEARCH["Web search"]:::searchCall
            REL["Relevance screening"]:::llmCall
            FETCH["Fetch sources"]:::searchCall
            FRETRY["Fetch retry once\n(transient errors)"]:::searchCall
            EX["Extract evidence + scopes"]:::llmCall
            CHECK["Scope / derivative checks\n+ evidence filter"]:::neutral

            QGEN -->|"queries"| SEARCH -->|"search results"| REL -->|"relevant URLs"| FETCH -->|"fetched sources"| EX -->|"evidence items + scopes"| CHECK
            FETCH -.->|"timeout / network / 5xx"| FRETRY -->|"retried fetch"| FETCH
        end

        CONTRA{"Contradiction\niterations left?"}:::decision
        CONTRA_RUN["Contradiction iteration\n(pick least-contradicted claim)"]:::searchCall
        SKEW{"Evidence pool\nskewed?"}:::decision
        CONTRARIAN["Contrarian retrieval\n(for each claim)"]:::searchCall

        MAIN -->|"Yes"| PICK -->|"target claim"| QGEN
        CHECK -->|"updated evidence pool"| MAIN
        MAIN -->|"No"| CONTRA
        CONTRA -->|"Yes"| CONTRA_RUN -->|"contradicting evidence"| CONTRA
        CONTRA -->|"No"| SKEW
        SKEW -->|"Yes"| CONTRARIAN
    end

    subgraph S3["Stage 3: Boundary Clustering Loops"]
        direction LR
        NS{"Normalize scopes?"}:::decision
        NORM["LLM scope normalization"]:::llmCall
        CL["LLM clustering"]:::llmCall
        CAP{"Within max\nboundaries?"}:::decision
        MERGE["Merge closest boundaries"]:::neutral

        NS -->|"Yes: unique scopes"| NORM -->|"normalized scopes"| CL -->|"candidate boundaries"| CAP
        NS -->|"No: unique scopes"| CL
        CAP -->|"No"| MERGE -->|"merged boundaries"| CAP
    end

    subgraph S4["Stage 4: Verdict Loops"]
        direction TB
        ADV["Advocate"]:::llmCall

        subgraph PAR["Parallel branch"]
            direction LR
            SC["Self-consistency\n(run2 + run3)"]:::llmCall
            CH["Challenger"]:::llmCall
        end

        SCRETRY["Retry failed\nself-consistency run once"]:::llmCall
        REC["Reconciliation"]:::llmCall
        VAL["Grounding + direction\nvalidation"]:::llmCall
        VRETRY["Validation batch\nretry once"]:::llmCall
        REPAIR["Direction repair\n+ revalidate"]:::llmCall

        ADV -->|"advocate verdicts"| SC
        ADV -->|"advocate verdicts"| CH
        SC -.->|"run failure"| SCRETRY -->|"retried run"| SC
        SC -->|"consistency spread"| REC
        CH -->|"challenge document"| REC
        REC -->|"reconciled verdicts"| VAL
        VAL -.->|"batch failure"| VRETRY -->|"retried validation"| VAL
        VAL -.->|"direction issue\nand policy enabled"| REPAIR -->|"repaired verdict"| VAL
    end

    SRCAL45["Stage 4.5: SR Calibration\n(optional, disabled by default)"]:::llmCall
    FINAL["Stage 5: Aggregate + report\n(no control-flow loop)"]:::neutral

    ENOUGH -->|"Yes: AtomicClaims"| MAIN
    SKEW -->|"No: EvidenceItems"| NS
    CONTRARIAN -->|"expanded evidence pool"| NS
    CAP -->|"Yes: ClaimBoundaries + CoverageMatrix"| ADV
    VAL -->|"ClaimVerdicts"| SRCAL45
    SRCAL45 -->|"Calibrated verdicts"| FINAL

    style S1 fill:#e8f5e9,stroke:#2e7d32,color:#000
    style S2 fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f57f17,color:#000
    style S3 fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
    style S4 fill:#f3e5f5,stroke:#7b1fa2,color:#000
    style PAR fill:#fafafa,stroke:#d9d9d9,color:#000,stroke-dasharray:5 3
    classDef llmCall fill:#f3e5f5,stroke:#7b1fa2,color:#4a148c,stroke-width:1.8px
    classDef searchCall fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#e65100,color:#bf360c,stroke-width:1.8px
